{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":2000,"text":"We live in in a remarkable time,"},{"time":5000,"text":"the age of genomics."},{"time":8000,"text":"Your genome is the entire sequence of your DNA."},{"time":11000,"text":"Your sequence and mine are slightly different."},{"time":14000,"text":"That's why we look different."},{"time":16000,"text":"I've got brown eyes;"},{"time":18000,"text":"you might have blue or gray."},{"time":21000,"text":"But it's not just skin-deep."},{"time":23000,"text":"The headlines tell us"},{"time":25000,"text":"that genes can give us scary diseases,"},{"time":28000,"text":"maybe even shape our personality,"},{"time":31000,"text":"or give us mental disorders."},{"time":34000,"text":"Our genes seem to have"},{"time":37000,"text":"awesome power over our destinies."},{"time":41000,"text":"And yet, I would like to think"},{"time":44000,"text":"that I am more than my genes."},{"time":49000,"text":"What do you guys think?"},{"time":51000,"text":"Are you more than your genes?"},{"time":54000,"text":"(Audience: Yes.) Yes?"},{"time":58000,"text":"I think some people agree with me."},{"time":60000,"text":"I think we should make a statement."},{"time":62000,"text":"I think we should say it all together."},{"time":65000,"text":"All right: \"I'm more than my genes\" -- all together."},{"time":68000,"text":"Everybody: I am more than my genes."},{"time":72000,"text":"(Cheering)"},{"time":75000,"text":"Sebastian Seung: What am I?"},{"time":77000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":80000,"text":"I am my connectome."},{"time":85000,"text":"Now, since you guys are really great,"},{"time":87000,"text":"maybe you can humor me and say this all together too."},{"time":89000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":91000,"text":"Right. All together now."},{"time":93000,"text":"Everybody: I am my connectome."},{"time":98000,"text":"SS: That sounded great."},{"time":100000,"text":"You know, you guys are so great, you don't even know what a connectome is,"},{"time":102000,"text":"and you're willing to play along with me."},{"time":104000,"text":"I could just go home now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":107000,"text":"Well, so far only one connectome is known,"},{"time":110000,"text":"that of this tiny worm."},{"time":113000,"text":"Its modest nervous system"},{"time":115000,"text":"consists of just 300 neurons."},{"time":117000,"text":"And in the 1970s and '80s,"},{"time":119000,"text":"a team of scientists"},{"time":121000,"text":"mapped all 7,000 connections"},{"time":123000,"text":"between the neurons."},{"time":126000,"text":"In this diagram, every node is a neuron,"},{"time":128000,"text":"and every line is a connection."},{"time":130000,"text":"This is the connectome"},{"time":132000,"text":"of the worm C. elegans."},{"time":136000,"text":"Your connectome is far more complex than this"},{"time":139000,"text":"because your brain"},{"time":141000,"text":"contains 100 billion neurons"},{"time":143000,"text":"and 10,000 times as many connections."},{"time":146000,"text":"There's a diagram like this for your brain,"},{"time":148000,"text":"but there's no way it would fit on this slide."},{"time":152000,"text":"Your connectome contains one million times more connections"},{"time":155000,"text":"than your genome has letters."},{"time":158000,"text":"That's a lot of information."}]},{"cues":[{"time":160000,"text":"What's in that information?"},{"time":164000,"text":"We don't know for sure, but there are theories."},{"time":167000,"text":"Since the 19th century, neuroscientists have speculated"},{"time":170000,"text":"that maybe your memories --"},{"time":172000,"text":"the information that makes you, you --"},{"time":174000,"text":"maybe your memories are stored"},{"time":176000,"text":"in the connections between your brain's neurons."},{"time":180000,"text":"And perhaps other aspects of your personal identity --"},{"time":182000,"text":"maybe your personality and your intellect --"},{"time":185000,"text":"maybe they're also encoded"},{"time":187000,"text":"in the connections between your neurons."},{"time":191000,"text":"And so now you can see why I proposed this hypothesis:"},{"time":194000,"text":"I am my connectome."},{"time":197000,"text":"I didn't ask you to chant it because it's true;"},{"time":200000,"text":"I just want you to remember it."},{"time":202000,"text":"And in fact, we don't know if this hypothesis is correct,"},{"time":204000,"text":"because we have never had technologies"},{"time":206000,"text":"powerful enough to test it."},{"time":209000,"text":"Finding that worm connectome"},{"time":212000,"text":"took over a dozen years of tedious labor."},{"time":215000,"text":"And to find the connectomes of brains more like our own,"},{"time":218000,"text":"we need more sophisticated technologies, that are automated,"},{"time":221000,"text":"that will speed up the process of finding connectomes."},{"time":224000,"text":"And in the next few minutes, I'll tell you about some of these technologies,"},{"time":227000,"text":"which are currently under development"},{"time":229000,"text":"in my lab and the labs of my collaborators."}]},{"cues":[{"time":233000,"text":"Now you've probably seen pictures of neurons before."},{"time":236000,"text":"You can recognize them instantly"},{"time":238000,"text":"by their fantastic shapes."},{"time":241000,"text":"They extend long and delicate branches,"},{"time":244000,"text":"and in short, they look like trees."},{"time":247000,"text":"But this is just a single neuron."},{"time":250000,"text":"In order to find connectomes,"},{"time":252000,"text":"we have to see all the neurons at the same time."},{"time":255000,"text":"So let's meet Bobby Kasthuri,"},{"time":257000,"text":"who works in the laboratory of Jeff Lichtman"},{"time":259000,"text":"at Harvard University."},{"time":261000,"text":"Bobby is holding fantastically thin slices"},{"time":263000,"text":"of a mouse brain."},{"time":265000,"text":"And we're zooming in by a factor of 100,000 times"},{"time":269000,"text":"to obtain the resolution,"},{"time":271000,"text":"so that we can see the branches of neurons all at the same time."},{"time":275000,"text":"Except, you still may not really recognize them,"},{"time":278000,"text":"and that's because we have to work in three dimensions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":281000,"text":"If we take many images of many slices of the brain"},{"time":283000,"text":"and stack them up,"},{"time":285000,"text":"we get a three-dimensional image."},{"time":287000,"text":"And still, you may not see the branches."},{"time":289000,"text":"So we start at the top,"},{"time":291000,"text":"and we color in the cross-section of one branch in red,"},{"time":294000,"text":"and we do that for the next slice"},{"time":296000,"text":"and for the next slice."},{"time":298000,"text":"And we keep on doing that,"},{"time":300000,"text":"slice after slice."},{"time":303000,"text":"If we continue through the entire stack,"},{"time":305000,"text":"we can reconstruct the three-dimensional shape"},{"time":308000,"text":"of a small fragment of a branch of a neuron."},{"time":311000,"text":"And we can do that for another neuron in green."},{"time":313000,"text":"And you can see that the green neuron touches the red neuron"},{"time":315000,"text":"at two locations,"},{"time":317000,"text":"and these are what are called synapses."}]},{"cues":[{"time":319000,"text":"Let's zoom in on one synapse,"},{"time":321000,"text":"and keep your eyes on the interior of the green neuron."},{"time":324000,"text":"You should see small circles --"},{"time":326000,"text":"these are called vesicles."},{"time":329000,"text":"They contain a molecule know as a neurotransmitter."},{"time":332000,"text":"And so when the green neuron wants to communicate,"},{"time":334000,"text":"it wants to send a message to the red neuron,"},{"time":336000,"text":"it spits out neurotransmitter."},{"time":339000,"text":"At the synapse, the two neurons"},{"time":341000,"text":"are said to be connected"},{"time":343000,"text":"like two friends talking on the telephone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":347000,"text":"So you see how to find a synapse."},{"time":349000,"text":"How can we find an entire connectome?"},{"time":352000,"text":"Well, we take this three-dimensional stack of images"},{"time":355000,"text":"and treat it as a gigantic three-dimensional coloring book."},{"time":358000,"text":"We color every neuron in, in a different color,"},{"time":361000,"text":"and then we look through all of the images,"},{"time":363000,"text":"find the synapses"},{"time":365000,"text":"and note the colors of the two neurons involved in each synapse."},{"time":368000,"text":"If we can do that throughout all the images,"},{"time":371000,"text":"we could find a connectome."}]},{"cues":[{"time":374000,"text":"Now, at this point,"},{"time":376000,"text":"you've learned the basics of neurons and synapses."},{"time":378000,"text":"And so I think we're ready to tackle"},{"time":380000,"text":"one of the most important questions in neuroscience:"},{"time":384000,"text":"how are the brains of men and women different?"},{"time":387000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":389000,"text":"According to this self-help book,"},{"time":391000,"text":"guys brains are like waffles;"},{"time":393000,"text":"they keep their lives compartmentalized in boxes."},{"time":396000,"text":"Girls' brains are like spaghetti;"},{"time":399000,"text":"everything in their life is connected to everything else."},{"time":402000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":404000,"text":"You guys are laughing,"},{"time":406000,"text":"but you know, this book changed my life."},{"time":408000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":412000,"text":"But seriously, what's wrong with this?"},{"time":415000,"text":"You already know enough to tell me -- what's wrong with this statement?"},{"time":425000,"text":"It doesn't matter whether you're a guy or girl,"},{"time":428000,"text":"everyone's brains are like spaghetti."},{"time":431000,"text":"Or maybe really, really fine capellini with branches."},{"time":435000,"text":"Just as one strand of spaghetti"},{"time":437000,"text":"contacts many other strands on your plate,"},{"time":440000,"text":"one neuron touches many other neurons"},{"time":442000,"text":"through their entangled branches."},{"time":444000,"text":"One neuron can be connected to so many other neurons,"},{"time":447000,"text":"because there can be synapses"},{"time":449000,"text":"at these points of contact."},{"time":454000,"text":"By now, you might have sort of lost perspective"},{"time":457000,"text":"on how large this cube of brain tissue actually is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":460000,"text":"And so let's do a series of comparisons to show you."},{"time":463000,"text":"I assure you, this is very tiny. It's just six microns on a side."},{"time":468000,"text":"So, here's how it stacks up against an entire neuron."},{"time":471000,"text":"And you can tell that, really, only the smallest fragments of branches"},{"time":474000,"text":"are contained inside this cube."},{"time":477000,"text":"And a neuron, well, that's smaller than brain."},{"time":482000,"text":"And that's just a mouse brain --"},{"time":486000,"text":"it's a lot smaller than a human brain."},{"time":490000,"text":"So when show my friends this,"},{"time":492000,"text":"sometimes they've told me,"},{"time":494000,"text":"\"You know, Sebastian, you should just give up."},{"time":497000,"text":"Neuroscience is hopeless.\""},{"time":499000,"text":"Because if you look at a brain with your naked eye,"},{"time":501000,"text":"you don't really see how complex it is,"},{"time":503000,"text":"but when you use a microscope,"},{"time":505000,"text":"finally the hidden complexity is revealed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":510000,"text":"In the 17th century,"},{"time":512000,"text":"the mathematician and philosopher, Blaise Pascal,"},{"time":514000,"text":"wrote of his dread of the infinite,"},{"time":517000,"text":"his feeling of insignificance"},{"time":519000,"text":"at contemplating the vast reaches of outer space."},{"time":524000,"text":"And, as a scientist,"},{"time":526000,"text":"I'm not supposed to talk about my feelings --"},{"time":529000,"text":"too much information, professor."},{"time":531000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":533000,"text":"But may I?"},{"time":535000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":537000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":539000,"text":"I feel curiosity,"},{"time":541000,"text":"and I feel wonder,"},{"time":543000,"text":"but at times I have also felt despair."},{"time":547000,"text":"Why did I choose to study"},{"time":549000,"text":"this organ that is so awesome in its complexity"},{"time":552000,"text":"that it might well be infinite?"},{"time":554000,"text":"It's absurd."},{"time":556000,"text":"How could we even dare to think"},{"time":558000,"text":"that we might ever understand this?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":563000,"text":"And yet, I persist in this quixotic endeavor."},{"time":566000,"text":"And indeed, these days I harbor new hopes."},{"time":570000,"text":"Someday,"},{"time":572000,"text":"a fleet of microscopes will capture"},{"time":574000,"text":"every neuron and every synapse"},{"time":576000,"text":"in a vast database of images."},{"time":579000,"text":"And some day, artificially intelligent supercomputers"},{"time":582000,"text":"will analyze the images without human assistance"},{"time":585000,"text":"to summarize them in a connectome."},{"time":589000,"text":"I do not know, but I hope that I will live to see that day,"},{"time":593000,"text":"because finding an entire human connectome"},{"time":595000,"text":"is one of the greatest technological challenges of all time."},{"time":598000,"text":"It will take the work of generations to succeed."},{"time":602000,"text":"At the present time, my collaborators and I,"},{"time":605000,"text":"what we're aiming for is much more modest --"},{"time":607000,"text":"just to find partial connectomes"},{"time":609000,"text":"of tiny chunks of mouse and human brain."},{"time":612000,"text":"But even that will be enough for the first tests of this hypothesis"},{"time":615000,"text":"that I am my connectome."},{"time":620000,"text":"For now, let me try to convince you of the plausibility of this hypothesis,"},{"time":623000,"text":"that it's actually worth taking seriously."}]},{"cues":[{"time":627000,"text":"As you grow during childhood"},{"time":629000,"text":"and age during adulthood,"},{"time":632000,"text":"your personal identity changes slowly."},{"time":635000,"text":"Likewise, every connectome"},{"time":637000,"text":"changes over time."},{"time":640000,"text":"What kinds of changes happen?"},{"time":642000,"text":"Well, neurons, like trees,"},{"time":644000,"text":"can grow new branches,"},{"time":646000,"text":"and they can lose old ones."},{"time":649000,"text":"Synapses can be created,"},{"time":652000,"text":"and they can be eliminated."},{"time":655000,"text":"And synapses can grow larger,"},{"time":657000,"text":"and they can grow smaller."},{"time":660000,"text":"Second question:"},{"time":662000,"text":"what causes these changes?"},{"time":665000,"text":"Well, it's true."},{"time":667000,"text":"To some extent, they are programmed by your genes."},{"time":670000,"text":"But that's not the whole story,"},{"time":672000,"text":"because there are signals, electrical signals,"},{"time":674000,"text":"that travel along the branches of neurons"},{"time":676000,"text":"and chemical signals"},{"time":678000,"text":"that jump across from branch to branch."},{"time":680000,"text":"These signals are called neural activity."},{"time":683000,"text":"And there's a lot of evidence"},{"time":685000,"text":"that neural activity"},{"time":688000,"text":"is encoding our thoughts, feelings and perceptions,"},{"time":691000,"text":"our mental experiences."},{"time":693000,"text":"And there's a lot of evidence that neural activity"},{"time":696000,"text":"can cause your connections to change."},{"time":699000,"text":"And if you put those two facts together,"},{"time":702000,"text":"it means that your experiences"},{"time":704000,"text":"can change your connectome."},{"time":707000,"text":"And that's why every connectome is unique,"},{"time":709000,"text":"even those of genetically identical twins."},{"time":713000,"text":"The connectome is where nature meets nurture."},{"time":717000,"text":"And it might true"},{"time":719000,"text":"that just the mere act of thinking"},{"time":721000,"text":"can change your connectome --"},{"time":723000,"text":"an idea that you may find empowering."}]},{"cues":[{"time":729000,"text":"What's in this picture?"},{"time":733000,"text":"A cool and refreshing stream of water, you say."},{"time":737000,"text":"What else is in this picture?"},{"time":742000,"text":"Do not forget that groove in the Earth"},{"time":744000,"text":"called the stream bed."},{"time":747000,"text":"Without it, the water would not know in which direction to flow."},{"time":750000,"text":"And with the stream,"},{"time":752000,"text":"I would like to propose a metaphor"},{"time":754000,"text":"for the relationship between neural activity"},{"time":756000,"text":"and connectivity."},{"time":759000,"text":"Neural activity is constantly changing."},{"time":762000,"text":"It's like the water of the stream; it never sits still."},{"time":765000,"text":"The connections"},{"time":767000,"text":"of the brain's neural network"},{"time":769000,"text":"determines the pathways"},{"time":771000,"text":"along which neural activity flows."},{"time":773000,"text":"And so the connectome is like bed of the stream;"},{"time":778000,"text":"but the metaphor is richer than that,"},{"time":781000,"text":"because it's true that the stream bed"},{"time":784000,"text":"guides the flow of the water,"},{"time":786000,"text":"but over long timescales,"},{"time":788000,"text":"the water also reshapes the bed of the stream."},{"time":791000,"text":"And as I told you just now,"},{"time":793000,"text":"neural activity can change the connectome."},{"time":798000,"text":"And if you'll allow me to ascend"},{"time":800000,"text":"to metaphorical heights,"},{"time":803000,"text":"I will remind you that neural activity"},{"time":806000,"text":"is the physical basis -- or so neuroscientists think --"},{"time":808000,"text":"of thoughts, feelings and perceptions."},{"time":811000,"text":"And so we might even speak of"},{"time":813000,"text":"the stream of consciousness."},{"time":815000,"text":"Neural activity is its water,"},{"time":818000,"text":"and the connectome is its bed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":822000,"text":"So let's return from the heights of metaphor"},{"time":824000,"text":"and return to science."},{"time":826000,"text":"Suppose our technologies for finding connectomes"},{"time":828000,"text":"actually work."},{"time":830000,"text":"How will we go about testing the hypothesis"},{"time":832000,"text":"\"I am my connectome?\""},{"time":835000,"text":"Well, I propose a direct test."},{"time":838000,"text":"Let us attempt"},{"time":840000,"text":"to read out memories from connectomes."},{"time":843000,"text":"Consider the memory"},{"time":845000,"text":"of long temporal sequences of movements,"},{"time":848000,"text":"like a pianist playing a Beethoven sonata."},{"time":851000,"text":"According to a theory that dates back to the 19th century,"},{"time":854000,"text":"such memories are stored"},{"time":856000,"text":"as chains of synaptic connections inside your brain."},{"time":860000,"text":"Because, if the first neurons in the chain are activated,"},{"time":863000,"text":"through their synapses they send messages to the second neurons, which are activated,"},{"time":866000,"text":"and so on down the line,"},{"time":868000,"text":"like a chain of falling dominoes."},{"time":870000,"text":"And this sequence of neural activation"},{"time":872000,"text":"is hypothesized to be the neural basis"},{"time":875000,"text":"of those sequence of movements."}]},{"cues":[{"time":877000,"text":"So one way of trying to test the theory"},{"time":879000,"text":"is to look for such chains"},{"time":881000,"text":"inside connectomes."},{"time":883000,"text":"But it won't be easy, because they're not going to look like this."},{"time":886000,"text":"They're going to be scrambled up."},{"time":888000,"text":"So we'll have to use our computers"},{"time":890000,"text":"to try to unscramble the chain."},{"time":893000,"text":"And if we can do that,"},{"time":895000,"text":"the sequence of the neurons we recover from that unscrambling"},{"time":898000,"text":"will be a prediction of the pattern of neural activity"},{"time":901000,"text":"that is replayed in the brain during memory recall."},{"time":904000,"text":"And if that were successful,"},{"time":906000,"text":"that would be the first example of reading a memory from a connectome."}]},{"cues":[{"time":913000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":915000,"text":"What a mess --"},{"time":918000,"text":"have you ever tried to wire up a system"},{"time":920000,"text":"as complex as this?"},{"time":922000,"text":"I hope not."},{"time":924000,"text":"But if you have, you know it's very easy to make a mistake."},{"time":930000,"text":"The branches of neurons are like the wires of the brain."},{"time":932000,"text":"Can anyone guess: what's the total length of wires in your brain?"},{"time":939000,"text":"I'll give you a hint. It's a big number."},{"time":941000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":944000,"text":"I estimate, millions of miles,"},{"time":947000,"text":"all packed in your skull."},{"time":950000,"text":"And if you appreciate that number,"},{"time":952000,"text":"you can easily see"},{"time":954000,"text":"there is huge potential for mis-wiring of the brain."},{"time":956000,"text":"And indeed, the popular press loves headlines like,"},{"time":959000,"text":"\"Anorexic brains are wired differently,\""},{"time":961000,"text":"or \"Autistic brains are wired differently.\""},{"time":963000,"text":"These are plausible claims,"},{"time":965000,"text":"but in truth,"},{"time":967000,"text":"we can't see the brain's wiring clearly enough"},{"time":969000,"text":"to tell if these are really true."},{"time":971000,"text":"And so the technologies for seeing connectomes"},{"time":974000,"text":"will allow us to finally"},{"time":976000,"text":"read mis-wiring of the brain,"},{"time":978000,"text":"to see mental disorders in connectomes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":985000,"text":"Sometimes the best way to test a hypothesis"},{"time":988000,"text":"is to consider its most extreme implication."},{"time":991000,"text":"Philosophers know this game very well."},{"time":995000,"text":"If you believe that I am my connectome,"},{"time":998000,"text":"I think you must also accept the idea"},{"time":1001000,"text":"that death is the destruction"},{"time":1003000,"text":"of your connectome."},{"time":1007000,"text":"I mention this because there are prophets today"},{"time":1010000,"text":"who claim that technology"},{"time":1013000,"text":"will fundamentally alter the human condition"},{"time":1016000,"text":"and perhaps even transform the human species."},{"time":1019000,"text":"One of their most cherished dreams"},{"time":1022000,"text":"is to cheat death"},{"time":1024000,"text":"by that practice known as cryonics."},{"time":1026000,"text":"If you pay 100,000 dollars,"},{"time":1028000,"text":"you can arrange to have your body frozen after death"},{"time":1031000,"text":"and stored in liquid nitrogen"},{"time":1033000,"text":"in one of these tanks in an Arizona warehouse,"},{"time":1035000,"text":"awaiting a future civilization"},{"time":1037000,"text":"that is advanced to resurrect you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1041000,"text":"Should we ridicule the modern seekers of immortality,"},{"time":1043000,"text":"calling them fools?"},{"time":1045000,"text":"Or will they someday chuckle"},{"time":1047000,"text":"over our graves?"},{"time":1050000,"text":"I don't know --"},{"time":1052000,"text":"I prefer to test their beliefs, scientifically."},{"time":1055000,"text":"I propose that we attempt to find a connectome"},{"time":1057000,"text":"of a frozen brain."},{"time":1059000,"text":"We know that damage to the brain"},{"time":1061000,"text":"occurs after death and during freezing."},{"time":1063000,"text":"The question is: has that damage erased the connectome?"},{"time":1066000,"text":"If it has, there is no way that any future civilization"},{"time":1069000,"text":"will be able to recover the memories of these frozen brains."},{"time":1072000,"text":"Resurrection might succeed for the body,"},{"time":1074000,"text":"but not for the mind."},{"time":1076000,"text":"On the other hand, if the connectome is still intact,"},{"time":1079000,"text":"we cannot ridicule the claims of cryonics so easily."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1085000,"text":"I've described a quest"},{"time":1087000,"text":"that begins in the world of the very small,"},{"time":1090000,"text":"and propels us to the world of the far future."},{"time":1093000,"text":"Connectomes will mark a turning point in human history."},{"time":1097000,"text":"As we evolved from our ape-like ancestors"},{"time":1099000,"text":"on the African savanna,"},{"time":1101000,"text":"what distinguished us was our larger brains."},{"time":1105000,"text":"We have used our brains to fashion"},{"time":1107000,"text":"ever more amazing technologies."},{"time":1110000,"text":"Eventually, these technologies will become so powerful"},{"time":1113000,"text":"that we will use them to know ourselves"},{"time":1116000,"text":"by deconstructing and reconstructing"},{"time":1119000,"text":"our own brains."},{"time":1122000,"text":"I believe that this voyage of self-discovery"},{"time":1125000,"text":"is not just for scientists,"},{"time":1128000,"text":"but for all of us."},{"time":1130000,"text":"And I'm grateful for the opportunity to share this voyage with you today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1133000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1135000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}